children.text: To polish or not to polish. Thanks to your pregnancy hormones, your nails may have never looked better. Increased levels of estrogen and progesterone may make your nails stronger and grow faster. You may want to take advantage of your newfound nails with a manicure or pedicure. If getting a mani or pedi sounds like a nice way to treat yourself, you’re in luck. Both are considered safe during pregnancy. Whether you are getting your nails done professionally or are more of a do it yourself kind of girl, make sure the area you’re in is well ventilated. A few of the chemicals in nail polish including toluene and formaldehyde can irritate your eyes and throat, so avoid breathing them in as much as possible. Plus, the fumes may make you a bit queasy, especially if you have been fighting morning sickness. To decrease exposure to irritating chemicals, consider only having your nails done once a week or less. Keep in mind, there are also formaldehyde free products on the market, which may be something to consider. As far as acrylic nails, there are few if any studies on their safety in pregnancy. But since there are chemicals involved in applying and filling acrylic nails, you may want to skip the tips until after your baby is born.

The first six weeks of pregnancy went by pretty quickly! You’ve only known that you’re pregnant for a week or two, but some amazing things are happening inside you with your tiny, developing baby. Although your baby’s body is just a head and tail at this stage; however, little eyes, mouth and ears are growing. Moreover those arms and legs that will be moving around in the coming months are just in the form of tiny buds. These will soon turn into flipper-like hands and feet. If you’re curious about the size of your little one, you only need to compare him or her to something about the size of a grain of rice. It is at this stage that the neural tube closes in your baby’s back. Even though your baby’s heart is beating regularly, it is still too soon to hear the heartbeat.
Baby size guide: Grain of rice
